The '''Bahing''' are a subset of the Indigenous Kirat ethnic group, located widely in Okhaldhunga and Solukhumbu District. They can be found in some of the villages like Bulaadi, Chisopani, Moli, Pankhu, Bhaudure, Apsowra, Rangadeep,Bigutar, Mamkha, Narayasthan, Baruneshowe, Ratmate, Waksa, Lekh Kharka of the [[Okhaldhunga District]], and Nechabatase, Salyan of Solukhumbu & in some other districts of eastern [[Nepal]]. {{citation needed|date=January 2018}}

Their language, also named [[Bahing language|Bahing]], belongs to the family of [[Kiranti languages]], a subgroup of [[Tibeto-Burman language|Tibeto-Burman]]. They have two main festivals: Hong and Susu.<ref>[[Kirat Mundhum]]</ref>  The Bahing also worship in Nature.

