{{Infobox person | name = Mamdouh Abdel-Alim | image = Mamdouh Abdel-Alim.jpg | image_size = 200px | caption = | native_name = ممدوح عبد العليم | native_name_lang = ar | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date|1956|11|10|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Menoufia]], [[Egypt]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2016|01|05|1956|11|10|df=yes}} | death_place = [[Cairo]], [[Egypt]] | nationality = [[Egyptians|Egyptian]] | occupation = [[Actor]] | religion = | years_active = 1970–2014 }}
'''Mamdouh Abdel-Alim''' ({{lang-ar|ممدوح عبد العليم}}; 10 November 1956 – 5 January 2016) was an [[Egypt]]ian actor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elcinema.com/person/pr1083511/ |title=ممدوح عبدالعليم - السينما.كوم |website=Elcinema.com |date=2015-02-25 |accessdate=2016-01-07}}</ref>
==Early career== His artistic career began as a child, performing in children's radio and television programming, schooled by director [[Inam Mohammed Ali]]. He then was schooled by the light [[Eldemerdash]] director, where he appeared as a small child in the series ''[[Paradise Virgin]]'' with actress [[Karima Mokhtar]]. He began his career in acting effectively in 1980, as a young man in the TV series ''[[Authentic (TV series)|Authentic]]'' along with Mokhtar, and in 1983 began acting in cinema in the film ''[[The Virgin and The White Hair]]".
==Death== He died on 5 January 2016 during practice for sports exercises in gym of [[Gezira Sporting Club]] in [[Cairo]], where he had a sudden heart attack and was taken to hospital and died there.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alaan.tv/news/celebrities/146118/the-departure-of-the-egyptian-artist-mamdouh-abdel-alim |title=رحيل الفنان المصري ممدوح عبد العليم &#124; الآن |website=Alaan.tv |date= |accessdate=2016-01-07}}</ref>
