{{Expand French|Musée Honmè|date=February 2018}}
The '''Royal Palace''', also known as '''King Toffa's Palace''' and more recently '''Musée Honmé''', is a former royal residence and today museum in [[Porto-Novo]], [[Benin]]. It contains an example of an [[Alounloun]] and most displays are related to the [[King Toffa]] period.<ref name="KrausReid2010">{{cite book|last1=Kraus|first1=Erika|last2=Reid|first2=Felicie|title=Benin (Other Places Travel Guide)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=op5eAvnZfG0C&pg=PA113|accessdate=14 June 2011|date=26 January 2010|publisher=Other Places Publishing|isbn=978-0-9822619-1-0|page=113}}</ref> The palace and the surrounding district was added to the [[UNESCO]] [[World Heritage]] Tentative List on October 31, 1996 in the Cultural category.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://whc.unesco.org/en/tentativelists/871/|title=La ville de Porto-Novo : quartiers anciens et Palais Royal (#) - UNESCO World Heritage Centre|last=Centre|first=UNESCO World Heritage|website=whc.unesco.org|language=en|access-date=2018-02-09}}</ref>
